                <head>265. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The First Committee of the <gloss target="#t_UN1">U.N.</gloss> General Assembly
                    discussed proposals for disarmament from October 13 to December 20, 1960, under
                    four general categories: general and complete disarmament, specific disarmament
                    proposals, prevention of nuclear weapons proliferation, and suspension of
                    nuclear testing. For the major statements and texts of resolutions considered by
                    the First Committee, see <hi rend="italic">Documents on Disarmament, 1960</hi>,
                    pages 297–372. The General Assembly adopted three resolutions as recommended by
                    the First Committee, Resolutions 1576–1578. For texts, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >ibid</hi>., pages 373–375.</p>
            </div>
